# Minimum Falling Path Sum

Platform: LeetCode 931  
Category: Dynamic Programming (Grid DP)

## Problem

Given an n x n matrix of integers, return the minimum sum of any falling path through the matrix.

You can move from cell (i,j) to:

- (i+1, j)   → Down
- (i+1, j-1) → Left Diagonal
- (i+1, j+1) → Right Diagonal

---

## Approaches

### 1. Recursion

Time Complexity: O(3^n)  
Reason: From each cell we explore 3 directions.

Space Complexity: O(n)  
Reason: Recursion stack depth equals number of rows.

---

### 2. Memoization (Top Down DP)

Time Complexity: O(n²)

Reason: Each state (i,j) computed once.

Space Complexity: O(n²) + O(n)

n² → DP table  
n → recursion stack

---

### 3. Tabulation (Bottom Up)

Time Complexity: O(n²)

Space Complexity: O(n²)

We fill the DP table row by row.

---

### 4. Space Optimized DP

Time Complexity: O(n²)

Space Complexity: O(n)

Only previous row is stored.

---

## Concepts Used

Grid DP  
State Transition  
Space Optimization
